 important his life had been. A new foreword by Marc Grossman considers the significance of Chavez's legacy for our time. As well as serving as an indispensable guide to the 1960s, this book rejuvenates the extraordinary vitality of Chavez's life and spirit, giving his message a renewed and much-needed urgency.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAgricultural laborersxLabor unionsxHistoryxUnited StatesxUnited States. 0aAgricultural laborers--Labor unions--United States--History. 0aChavez Cesar--1927-1993. 0aHispanic American civic leaders--California. 0aLabor leadersxBiographyxUnited States. 0aMatthiessen Peter. 0aMexican American agricultural laborersxHistory. 0aMexican American agricultural laborers--History. 0aMexican AmericansxBiography. 0aMexican Americans--California--Social conditions. 0aUnited Farm Workers--History. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Political.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311062111208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package 2014-2016z978311065748740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520958364423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520958364.jpg  a978-3-11-062111-2  UC Press eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  a978-3-11-065748-7  UCal Press eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles